  "prompt": "How much time does Wipro takes to send a DOJ after the background verification is done?",
  "response": "The time Wipro takes to send a Date of Joining (DOJ) after the background verification can vary based on several factors, including the role, location, and any specific organizational processes. Generally, it may take anywhere from a few days to a few weeks. If the background verification is completed smoothly without issues, candidates can expect to receive their DOJ soon after. However, keep in mind that delays can occur due to administrative reasons, internal approvals, or other procedural steps.\n\nFor the most accurate and tailored information, it's best to directly contact Wipro's HR or recruitment team, as they can provide the most relevant details based on your specific situation.",
